tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE model_performance ( 
    performance_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, 
    model_name TEXT, 
    accuracy FLOAT, 
    precision FLOAT, 
    recall FLOAT 
);

CREATE TABLE training_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    features TEXT,
    label TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE training_data (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  feature1 FLOAT,
  feature2 FLOAT,
  target FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE model_parameters (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  parameter_name VARCHAR(255),
  parameter_value FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE model_performance (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  evaluation_date TIMESTAMP,
  accuracy FLOAT,
  loss FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE training_history (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  training_date TIMESTAMP,
  epochs INT,
  time_taken FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE validation_data (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  feature1 FLOAT,
  feature2 FLOAT,
  target FLOAT
)
